        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is Mangools good for beginners?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — it is the cleanest, most beginner-friendly SEO suite on the market. KWFinder makes low-competition keyword research genuinely simple, and the interface avoids the feature bloat of Semrush and Ahrefs." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Mangools vs Ahrefs — which is better?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Ahrefs has a much larger backlink index, deeper SERP data, and serious features for professionals. Mangools is 1/3 the price, much easier to learn, and covers the basics 90% of small operators need. Pick Mangools for budget + simplicity; Ahrefs for professional-grade depth." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does Mangools write content?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Mangools is a research-only suite. It finds keywords, tracks rankings, and analyses competitors — but does not write, edit, or publish anything. You still need writers and a publishing workflow." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does the KWFinder tool do?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KWFinder is the headline tool. It surfaces low-competition keywords by combining search volume, difficulty score, CPC, trend, and SERP analysis in one clean interface. The KD score is widely regarded as more accurate for low-competition niches than Ahrefs' KD." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is there a free trial?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — 10-day free trial with full access to all 5 tools, no credit card required up front in some markets. The free trial is enough to test the full workflow on a real site." }},
