        <h2 id="what-is">What is Mangools?</h2>
        <p>Mangools is a 5-tool SEO suite built for beginners, bloggers, and small agencies. It started as KWFinder in August 2014, built by Peter Hrbáčik in Bratislava, Slovakia. The Mangools brand launched in May 2016 as a unified platform. Today it serves <strong>1.1 million+ registered users across 160+ countries</strong>.</p>

        <p>The company is bootstrapped — no venture capital, no investors, no IPO. The team is under 40 people. The product philosophy: simple beats complex.</p>

        <p>The suite includes:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>KWFinder</strong> — keyword research with the cleanest difficulty score in the budget tier</li>
          <li><strong>SERPChecker</strong> — analyse the top 10 results for any keyword</li>
          <li><strong>SERPWatcher</strong> — daily rank tracking with the simplest dashboard in SEO</li>
          <li><strong>LinkMiner</strong> — backlink analysis powered by partner data</li>
          <li><strong>SiteProfiler</strong> — domain authority + competitive analysis snapshot</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Mangools is <em>not</em>: a content tool, a publisher, or a local SEO platform.</p>

        <h2 id="features">Mangools features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. KWFinder — the headline tool</h3>
        <p>KWFinder is why people pay for Mangools. Enter a seed keyword and get a clean list of related terms with monthly volume, difficulty, CPC, trend, and a SERP snapshot. The difficulty score is widely regarded as more accurate for low-competition niches than Ahrefs KD. For finding hidden 300–800 volume keywords, KWFinder is unbeatable at this price.</p>

        <h3>2. SERPChecker — analyse the top 10</h3>
        <p>For any keyword, SERPChecker pulls the top 10 results with DA, PA, Citation Flow, Trust Flow, Facebook shares, and a difficulty score. The most useful feature: side-by-side comparison of multiple SERP positions to spot patterns.</p>

        <h3>3. SERPWatcher — rank tracking</h3>
        <p>Daily position updates with the simplest dashboard in the category. Performance Index aggregates your rankings into a single trend line. Mobile / desktop split, local tracking, and weekly email reports included on all plans.</p>

        <h3>4. LinkMiner — backlink analysis</h3>
        <p>Powered by partner backlink data. Smaller index than Ahrefs or Majestic, but Link Strength (a proprietary 1–100 quality score) is genuinely useful for spotting the high-value links in a profile.</p>

        <h3>5. SiteProfiler — competitive snapshot</h3>
        <p>One-page overview of any domain: estimated traffic, top keywords, top pages, link profile summary, and competitor list. Great for fast competitive recon — not for deep analysis.</p>

